<br>
<br>
As for the George Carlin quote, I would like to point out that I personally support most of the so-called &quot;liberal&quot; social programs.  Care should not end at birth, WIC is great, school lunch programs, medicare, etc.  I support all of these.  On most individual issues I side with the liberal position far more often than the conservative one, abortion being the most notable exception.  If you had to pidgeonhole me into some sort of political stereotype, I'd probably fit in best as a pro-life democrat.  I hold no party affilation, and doubt I ever will, and I vote republican, green, and libertarian on occasion, but in the context of the two major US parties, I fall in with the Democratic view far more often than the republican one.  <br>
<br>
I see the reverse of the Carlin position as being true.  Democrats wax eloquent about caring for the child in umpteen ways after it is born, yet they extend no protection to the unborn fetus.  This to me is the truely puzzling position.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uuraniumcw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>UraniumCW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/15/01 12:35:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Abortion 2 Foetus 2 Person</span><hr size=1> I didn't dodge the question at all.  You didn't read the answer.  :^)<br>
<br>
It's right here:<br>
<br>
***<br>
If I walked over to your house and beat the crap out of your dog (presuming you have one), is that wrong? Is it illegal? Will I be punished? Yes, yes and yes. Is it because I have violated the dogs rights or yours? Should the dog have rights?<br>
<br>
Where's the difference? Dog or fetus, it's a subset of your own personal rights and should be treated as such. If I kill your fetus, I've killed a part of you and it should be punished as such. <br>
***<br>
<br>
You could easily have fetus murder/damage/injury laws and have them be punishable without granting the fetus &quot;rights&quot;.  I agree it would be a heinous crime and should be punished.  I question whether the fetus needs rights assigned or granted to it.<br>
<br>
I contend that until successfully born, the fetus is an object and property of the person carrying it, possibly with some rights of property to the other person involved in the conception.  <br>
<br>
I realize this is arbitrary, harsh and somewhat extreme.  I know there are parents out there that have heard their fetus's heartbeat at 13 weeks, and seen ultrasounds and will be horrified by the term &quot;property&quot;.  Too bad, it's an opinion.  <br>
<br>
The whole abortion issue tends to revolve around when to declare the fetus a human being, not whether or not the fetus deserves protection.  If it's just another cell in your body, it gets nothing.  When it's human it's get what everyone else gets.  When does the change over take place?  At the first sign fertilization?  At the first sign of cell mitosis? At the first independant movement of the baby?  When the cortex forms? Upon birth?  There's a logical reason for all of them, and we won't all agree on one, there's no &quot;average&quot; answer.<br>
<br>
Pick an arbitrary time and run with it.  I don't think it's a black and white issue.  It's grey from 3 weeks to 7 months or so.  Before 3 weeks, it's pretty much a cell, after 7 months or so it's pretty obviously a baby.  In between, what is it?  When does it change?  Err on the side of the fetus's rights and say it's always a baby or err on the side of the mothers rights and give her control over her own body?<br>
<br>
My main problem with abortion laws in the fact that they restrict what you can do with your own body.  It's legal to smoke, do hard drugs and drink while pregnant, that's your right (killing it slowly in the long run).  But you can't terminate a pregnancy (killing it quickly).  <br>
<br>
I think it's despicable to do something like that to a fetus (drink, smoke).  I think abortions should only be allowed up until a certain term of the pregnancy (once again - arbitrary).  I think people that abort at 8 months should be shot.  I think people that intentionally harm fetuses are underdeveloped in some way.<br>
<br>
In your state, killing a fetus is murder.  I applaud that.  At what age do they consider it a &quot;fetus&quot;?  I am curious.  Is it at 1 second, 1 day, 1 week, 1 month?  What's the arbitrary definition adopted by your state lawyers?<br>
<br>
Admittedly percentages would be hard to apply to something like this.  But the general idea is there.  The fetus imediately gets protection against aggresive acts (as in assault and murder) but it's right to be born only comes the longer in develops.  Just a thought.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sorry this was a mess of thoughts all slapped together.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
George Carlin was funny and extreme of course but it does point out a lack of consistency.  I always balk at any categorizing or pigeon-holing.  I'm not conservative, I'm not liberal, I'm me.  I have some views that go one way, some another all based on my own personal ethics.  As a result, the Carlin bit is merely humor and not actually representative of anything other than Rex's bad taste in comics.  Weird Al Yankovic sucks too.<br>
