<br>
I'm about 99% sure that the particular state law I was using as an example extends the rights to the fetus at 3 months.  <br>
<br>
To me, once everything has come to place (sperm, egg, sexy music, etc.) to create that 1 cell zygote that contains everything necessary to create a human, that is the point at which a separate life forms within the mother.  This life, imo, has a right to be allowed the chance to be born into the world.  I personally would not accord full &quot;human&quot; rights to a developing fetus, but I feel that some rights should be accorded to it.  Mainly, the right for a chance to make it.  <br>
<br>
